Arctic Monkeys postponed Glasgow concert due to Alex Turner's illness
Rock band Arctic Monkeys moved up the concert in Glasgow after the main singer was diagnosed with larygreze inflammation.
The Sheffield group was scheduled to perform at the Hydro City Complex on Friday.
But the disease of lead singer Alexa Turner forced her to move the performance.
The group's announcement came after it was similarly forced to postpone Thursday's performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham.
In a statement on their official website, the Arctic Monkeys group says: "After the decision to postpone today's appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham, and on the basis of medical advice, the Arctic Monkeys must also postpone the appearance at the Hydro in Glasgow complex scheduled for Friday 1 November."
"Alex Turner has been diagnosed with laryngeal inflammation and, unfortunately, he will not be able to disperse."
The performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham will thus take place on 20 November and a performance at the Hydro complex in Glasgow on 21 November.
All tickets for these performances remain valid.
